The Munsell color entered (light greenish grey, 5GY 7/1) is the dominant color, with the top of the section 0-29 cm following on the color of the previous section (very pale brown, 10YR 7/3). The contact between the two colors is gradational over 15 cm (roughly 30-45 cm) and is preceded by a lighter very pale brown interval from 9-21 cm.  Large chondrites burrows are observed from 22-28 cm. A tan horizon occurs at 6 cm.

Moderately to heavily bioturbated. Fainter green interval from 0-38 and 67-111 cm with more abundant brown mottles (particularly from 0-26 and 67-97 cm). Green glaconitic horizons at 70-71 and 77-78 cm. Greener intervals (38-67 and 111-150 cm) are heavily bioturbated.

Moderately to heavily bioturbated. Fainter green interval from 0-56 cm and   more abundant brown mottles from 0-38 and 89-125 cm. Green glaconitic horizons at 7-8, 17-18,  and 90-92 cm. Interval in between the noted brown bioturbation are heavily bioturbated.

Moderately to heavily bioturbated with more abundant small burrows than in preceding sections. Decimeter scale banding in bioturbation and slight background variation in lightness/darkness. Occasional sulfide blebs.
